在[[字体排印学|字体排印学]]中，'''字怀'''（又称'''字谷'''）指字母构造中的全封闭或半封闭区域。<ref>{{cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?ei=Py1jSuyoH4nAzQT_1rn1CA&id=1cyy76-taU4C&dq=typography+counter&q=counter|title=Using desktop publishing to create newsletters, handouts, and Web pages|publisher=Neal-Schuman|accessdate=July 19, 2009|year=1997|isbn=978-1-55570-265-6|page=33|format=Google books (snippet view)|quote=Counter is the white space center of enclosed letters like Bb, Dd, Pp.|last1=Maxymuk|first1=John|trans_title=|archive-date=2019-08-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190812121741/https://books.google.com/books?ei=Py1jSuyoH4nAzQT_1rn1CA&id=1cyy76-taU4C&dq=typography+counter&q=counter|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=zVUCxdx7QYcC&pg=PA74&dq=typography+counter+aperture&as_brr=3&ei=HS5jSsXAMpnCzgTk7OyuDQ|title=Designing Websites: According to the Ancient Science of Directions|last2=|first2=|date=|publisher=Smita Jain Narang|accessdate=July 19, 2009|others=|year=2006|isbn=978-81-207-3071-7|edition=|series=|volume=|location=|page=74|language=|format=Google books (limited prview)|quote=Open space in a letter is called the counter or the aperture.|last1=Narang|first1=Sumita|authorlink1=|editor1-first=|editor1-last=|editor1-link=|archive-date=2019-08-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190811154257/https://books.google.com/books?id=zVUCxdx7QYcC&pg=PA74&dq=typography+counter+aperture&as_brr=3&ei=HS5jSsXAMpnCzgTk7OyuDQ|dead-url=no}}</ref> [[拉丁字母|拉丁字母]]中包含有封闭字怀的有A、B、D、O、P、Q、R、a、b、d、e、g、o、p和q， 包含开放字怀的有c、f、h、s等，数字0、4、6、8、9同样拥有字怀。字怀与字母外部空间之间的开口称为'''字怀开口'''。

小写字母[[G|“g”有两种印刷变体]]：单层“[[File:Opentail_g.svg|14x14像素]]”有一个封闭字怀和一个开放字怀；双层“[[File:Looptail_g.svg|12x12像素]]”有两个封闭字怀。

数字4同样有两种印刷变体：上封闭的“[[File:4.svg|25x25像素]]”有一个封闭字怀，上开放（即手写体）的“[[File:Four_handwritten.svg|14x14像素]]”有一个开放字怀。

== 开口的开放和闭合 ==
不同字体在设计时会有不同的开口大小取向，而开口大小的选取对[[无衬线体|无衬线体]]的设计又有着至关重要的作用。在有些无衬线体的设计之中，笔画取粗而开口取狭。
[[File:Typeface_apertures.png|替代=Images of the typefaces Corbel, Helvetica and Haettenschweiler.]]的对比： Corbel 具外放的开口，[[Helvetica|Helvetica]]的则较为封闭，Haettenschweiler同样封闭，而且更加紧缩。注意，Haettenschweiler的数字8和数字9很难分辨。]]
追求易认性（legibility）的字体通常开口外放。为避免相近字符被误认，追求易认性的字体常被设计得笔画舒展，布局匀称。在有些应用场合，这一设计变得尤为重要；比如需要远观的标识、为视力障碍者准备的阅读材料或低质量印刷的小字内容。<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.typography.com/fonts/mercury-text/features/mercury-efficiency|title=Mercury Text: Features|accessdate=28 November 2014|publisher=Hoefler & Frere-Jones|archive-date=2016-10-16|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161016025811/http://www.typography.com/fonts/mercury-text/features/mercury-efficiency|dead-url=no}}</ref> 具有开放开口的字体既包括用于低分辨率屏幕显示的字体，比如[[Lucida_Grande|Lucida Grande]]、[[Trebuchet_MS|Trebuchet MS]]、{{link-en|Corbel|Corbel}}和[[Droid|Droid Sans]]，也有诸如[[Frutiger|Frutiger]]和{{link-en|FF Meta|FF Meta}}这些设计用于印刷的字体。<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://blog.typekit.com/2013/04/11/three-exemplary-typefaces-for-user-interfaces/|title=Three Exemplary Typefaces for User Interfaces|accessdate=28 November 2014|last=Whited|first=Billy|publisher=Adobe|archive-date=2014-12-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141204233729/http://blog.typekit.com/2013/04/11/three-exemplary-typefaces-for-user-interfaces/|dead-url=no}}</ref>自1980年代和1990年代人文主义无衬线体开始大行其道， 外放开口的设计变得越来越普遍，计算机屏幕显示的需要正是该设计的流行原因之一。{{Quote box|align=right|width=30%|quote=Helvetica并不是万灵药……它难以胜任排印小字……“C”和“S”的形状卷得太多，使得开口太紧——字怀开口是指沟通字母内外的那片空白……小写字母“e”是英语当中最常见的字母，而Helvetica选取了一种最不讨喜的形状。（在小字下，）像这样的字母距离被误识的境地只有一像素之遥。|source=[[Tobias_Frere-Jones|Tobias Frere-Jones]]<ref>{{cite web|last1=Covert|first1=Adrian|title=Why Apple's New Font Won't Work On Your Desktop|url=http://www.fastcodesign.com/3031432/why-apples-new-font-wont-work-on-your-desktop|website=FastCoDesign|accessdate=28 November 2014|archive-date=2017-07-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170706205422/https://www.fastcodesign.com/3031432/why-apples-new-font-wont-work-on-your-desktop|dead-url=no}}</ref>}}“新无衬线体”，比如[[Helvetica|Helvetica]]的开口较为紧致，笔画末端被折叠得彼此十分靠近。这让其设计变得独特而紧凑，但也牺牲了相近字母的可区分程度。趋向于闭合和高度紧缩的字体，比如[[Impact|Impact]]、{{link-en|Haettenschweiler|Haettenschweiler}}，在小字印刷某些文字时，譬如数字“8”和数字“9”会变得难以分辨。设计师{{link-en|Nick Shinn|Nick Shinn}}指出，这一设计趋势之于无衬线体，类似于19世纪时的{{link-en|Didone|Didone}}之于衬线体，可能是为了分散活字上的压力以减小活字磨损。<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://shinntype.com/wp-content/uploads/files/pdf/Scotch_Modern.pdf|title=Modern Suite|accessdate=11 August 2015|last=Shinn|first=Nick|publisher=Shinntype|archive-date=2021-02-25|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210225042806/http://shinntype.com/wp-content/uploads/files/pdf/Scotch_Modern.pdf|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.typotheque.com/articles/my_type_design_philosophy |title=My Type Design Philosophy by Martin Majoor |accessdate=2017-02-19 |archive-date=2020-01-14 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200114232207/https://www.typotheque.com/articles/my_type_design_philosophy |dead-url=no }}</ref>

